\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Arthur. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 2 Eastbridge Avenue, Sneyd Green, Stoke on Trent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And your marital status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 The year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 1932.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 The year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 1904.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Cobridge, Stoke on Trent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I should say only a few months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where did you live after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 After that I lived in - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 Co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 bridge Road, Hanley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 For how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And that would be something in the region of - see, from about one to - twelve or thirteen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember why the family made this move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 At a few months old? I'm sorry, I couldn't tell you that. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes, I had a half brother, the eldest of the family. A sister who came next and a brother - and I'm the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember your father's age when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - let me see. He died when he was ninety-three - ninety-two rather. Yes. He's been dead about - h
e died in 1964. So that would put him - sixty-four - '64 - 93 is 29 years isn't it. He was born about 1970 - 1871.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 1904. So that's twenty-nine - thirty-three roughly isn't it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well I believe the family originated in Silverdale. Near to Newcastle - Stoke on Trent - Newcastle. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well for many years he was a foreman baker. Then he had a period of unemployment. And - he became - an insurance agent. 
And he continued as an insurance agent until he - he retired. Well he was over - something over seventy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 He was a foreman baker for quite some while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was that his first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 That was his - as far as I knew, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And afterwards he became an insurance agent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 An insurance agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did he have any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 None whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember him being out of work for any length of time? Was there a long period between him being in the bakery and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 becoming}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  an insurance agent?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Yes, it might have lasted - something in the region - of twelve months or so when he was out of work. That was from the time he - you see - he had a - a bad dose of sciatica and by the time he was fit for work ag
ain his job had gone. Then he had a period of several months out of work and then he took up this insurance agent business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So would he be working at the baker in 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, definitely so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember your mother's age when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Mother's age, now mother died - mother died 1953 I think and she was eighty-two. Now we shall have to work back from there shan't we. She was eighty-two in 1953. So that's another twenty-nine years isn't it. So she'd be born somewhere abo
ut the same year - 1871. So more or less - more or less the same age as my father. Thirty-three, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And she came from - she came from Boodle, Hanley, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 Stoke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  on Trent. But - her parents - at least her father, came from South Wales.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did she work before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I believe she did but - yes, she did work before she was married. And she worked a little firm of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 tobacconist\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  in Bryant Street, Hanley, their name was Keene's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember her working after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did she ever have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 She never worked after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 While I was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 child,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember how many rooms there were in the house in Cobridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 It was a
 three bedroomed house. Terrace type. The normal - the normal type of house for the ordinary working class family at that time. Three bedroomed house and was one, two - there's a front room, what we used to call the kitchen which was the living room and w
hat we - what is now termed the scullery you see and the - the facilities, toilet and coal house and things were outside. There was no bathroom there, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 For most 
of the time, no. For one short period - how long it was - a few months I should think - we had my father's - my grandfather - my paternal grandfather staying with us for a few months. But for the majority of the time it was a self contained family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. Couldn't afford to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes, definitely. Done at home. By my mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother or father mend or make any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Possibly mother - did a bit of sewing. But not - not as a regular thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 The family's clothes were bought were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 More or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were they new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes, oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember where they were bought, what sort of shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh she'd go to such places as Bratt and Dykes in Hanley and the old firm - the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 \endash McIlroy\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  which is now at Lewis's, and possibly one or two of the smaller - drapers and haberdashers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But always new clothes and always from clothing outfitters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 More or less so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember how often clothes were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well - speaking for myself in those days we - we came from a Non-conformist family and the - the anniversary was the - the highlight in the - in the domestic year. That's right. So that, more or less, any new clothes you had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 coincided}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 with that - with the anniversary. Yes. That was about the only time generally except for shoes and - perhaps an odd pair of trousers and things that wore out in the meantime, that was the only time we had, shall we say, a new outfit. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were shoes always new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 But very, very often - repaired. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Soled and heeled and things like that, but they were always new shoes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where would she buy those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I suppose in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 usual}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  places in - in Hanley, the usual }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 shoe shops}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 I'm afraid not, because when he was a baker - he was for many, many years working nights you see, so that
 more or less his daytime was - was sleeping.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about decorating, repairs and improvements to the property?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well the - the house was - the house was - if I remember rightly was a rented house. Hut any interior decorating we had to do ourselve
s. Me father would do that with me mother's help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember your father dressing you and undressing you as children or reading to you and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. Never, because - apart - he had two main interests in life, one was his work and the other was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 - his Sunday school and church. Those were his only two interests and they took up all his time and as a - as a father, although he was a good father, he never had - he never spent much time with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did he ever take you out without }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 your mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I doubt it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about looking after you when your mother was out for some reason.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 We looked after ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - I was the youngest.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Is there a big difference in age between you and the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Between me and the eldest. Well the eldest, he's still living down in - in Devon, my half brother that is, he would be in the region of something like ten years older than I am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You say he is your half brother, how?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 My father's second marriage. Yes. One child from the first marriage, yes. The other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 three,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  sister and brother and myself. Two brothers - two male children and one - one sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But he was brought up as a brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 Well - for many, many years my half brother lived with my grandparents. With my father's parents, for many, many years. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 It's only - a few years previous to the outbreak of the first world war that he came back to - to live with us as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your father lose his first wife or were they divorced or was it never discussed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 There was very, very little mention made of it at home but I believe my father's first wife died.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So you can't ever remember him looking after you children while your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. No, no recollection of it whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So although you say he was a good man he didn't spend a lot of time at home with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have any tasks at home in the house that you had to carry our regularly to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - probably running some errands and - perhaps getting the coal in and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother do the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I should imagine so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How long did you continue to do these things, after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, within reason, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did the other children have chores that they had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I suppose they did, as far as I can - I can recollect, yes. But they were not - not regular }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 chores}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 , just as - just as occasion arose, one of the others would be delegated to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember the older children helping you with the things you found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Not particularly, my sister was seven years older than I was - my other full brother was four and a half years. Yes, yes. Yes, yes. My sister was seven years older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 Would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  she help you to dress and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I couldn't - I couldn't remember. I wouldn't know. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember any way in which the younger children might help the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I suppose they were normal in - in that respect. Certainly not abnormal, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time during schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Those were the days when - parental discipline and especially in - in - in our family was pretty strict. My father was b
rought up in a strict school and - that somewhat Victorian attitude to the - the duty of children to their parents was more or less adhered to in the household. Yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 
Yes, we were never out very, very late. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In summer when it was going dusk we were supp
osed to be in the house. And in winter when it went dark rather early, well - perhaps seven o'clock or so. Certainly before eight we were due in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember how long it would continue that you had to go to bed at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I 
suppose as we got older the - the extensions became a bit longer. But beyond that - I would say - I would say even - even to the time when we were - we were - approaching the late teens, we were supposed to be in the house, except on special occasions, by
 ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes, I should imagine, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember at what age you were able to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - I should say when I was - seven, eight or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 nineish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have to share a bedroom or a bed with anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Yes, for many years I shared a - a bed with my brother. You'd have to you see because mother and father in one room, the two brothers in the other room and - my sister in - in a room on her own you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You weren't overcrowded were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 A three bedroomed house was quite a good size?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Yes, and by the time my - my half brother came to live with us, my sister I think would have been - would be married by then you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - I have very early recollections of the old tin bath in front of the fire. That would be in the kitchen in front of the fire, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have regular bath nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was it one particular night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 Yes, more or less I think it was Friday night, Amami night. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you always have clean clothes to put on after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In what we used to term the - the kitchen. Because what we now term the scullery was always referred to as the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No. The front room was the parlour and that was only used on - special occasions. And perhaps on - on Sundays. Just for sitting about in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Your mother cooked in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In the - in the scullery. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did she cook on, with a range or with gas?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh now wait a minute, I might have to qualify that, going back, I can hardly remember the - the house in - in Cobridg
e Road. No, I think - no, those were the days when - in the - in the - what we referred as the - the kitchen, the living room, where we spent shall we say ninety-nine percent of our time, there was the old fashioned range with the oven on one side. The bl
a
ck - the old black - the old black iron stove - range - the old black range with the oven and so the - the kitchen - the - the cooking was done in what we referred to as the living room or the kitchen. That's right, yes. And the scullery was only more or 
less probably be the old brick boiler there for the washing - washday and - and a sink you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So she didn't have a gas cooker as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh no, not in those days. No, not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 When would breakfast be eaten, would you all eat together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No, for the simple reason of me father coming in shall we say about six or seven o'clock in the morning, would probably - have his breakfast, his meal and go to bed. And we, the rest of the family would more or less eat together then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So this would be the three or four children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, there'd only be three of us. The three children and my mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember what you usually had for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh goodness knows. There'd be toast, there'd be marmalade, there'd be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 bacon
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 I suppose. Those were the days before cereals weren't they, you see. Yes, those - those were the days before the - the modern cereal foods were on the market you see, so more or less it was - bread and butter or toast and butter, marmalade and - and baco
n you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Bacon by itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Except perhaps on - on Sundays when it might be - yes. Perhaps a little bit extra on Sunday you see to - well perhaps an egg with it or tomatoes, something like that. Although a very favourite dish in those days would 
be - in the weekday possibly with the bacon might be some cheese, you see. Which I believe is somewhat peculiar to this district. I know, but I believe - yes, but I believe - I believe in some parts of the country if you say, I'll have some cheese with th
e
 bacon you know, cooked under the grill - it's somewhat odd in some parts of the country, yes, but it's a very favourite dish here. Yes. There was another favourite one for - for weekends too and that was the - the - the oatcake in this district, which - 
that is - that is another - another food }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 peculiar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 to this district. Yes. Well, when I used to go - at one time we used to visit my half brother in Devon. And one of the things we had to take with us was about a couple of dozen of these oatcakes because they couldn't get them there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 . Yes. Just like dialect is peculiar to a district, so certain types of food are. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 And I would say the cheese with bacon and oatcakes were -more or less - peculiar to this district.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What would you drink with breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - only tea. That's as a child don't forget. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about midday meals, what did you call your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In the midday meal - we used to call it dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What would you eat for dinner in the weekdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I suppose the - the 
usual run of things. Might be - occasionally might be bacon and cheese for dinner or it might occasionally be meat and - and veg. But apart from that I - I couldn't give you a clue now,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have pudding, dessert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. On occasions. Perhaps not regularly but perhaps two or three times a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would the midday meal on Sunday be different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Our midday meal on Sunday was a - a really - shall we say meat and two veg and pudding of some kind, sweet of some kind you see. Definitely. T
hat was the - that was, shall we say, the main meal of the week. Whereas the other - the other - the other midday meals during the week more or less were - may have been make do and mend kind of sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Who would be present at the weekday midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh, only the family. Then - then - we should probably all eat together, my father, mother and - and the children. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What would your evening meal be termed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh that - we always used to call that tea. That was tea. Weekday tea would 
- vary. From the very simple bread and jam to perhaps, occasionally, fruit - tinned fruit, which wasn't so - common as it is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 today}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  you see. But more or less they were - they were satisfying meals if they - if they were simple meals, see what I mean. But there was nothing - special or - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 
ostentatious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  about them because quite simply the - the family }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 budget}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  wouldn't allow it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about Sunday tea, would that be any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Now Sunday tea again, Sunday tea was - was more - more elaborate. The Sun
day, like the - the - the midday meal, the Sunday tea would be more - much more elaborate you see. Much more the kind of a - a tea that the average family would have today. That would be - that would be probably fruit - stewed fruit or tinned fruits, brea
d and butter, cake and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 The meals were breakfast dinner and tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Breakfast, dinner and tea, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember your mother or father baking their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Only very occasionally. Only very occasionally. I would say
 with regard to baking, me mother did most of the baking, tarts and cakes and things like that but at Christmas time, me father being a - a professional baker, he always made the Christmas cake. And also he always used to make the - a huge pork pie, which
 
he took to the - the bakery to have baked. See? And occasionally - as a - sometimes to - to help certain people out, perhaps friends or - or he has done it for the firm, he has - he has baked wedding cakes and decorated them. Well - he was - he was pretty
 
good if I - if I would fault him in one respect it would be that when he came to decoration he over decorated and - there might have been, shall we say, a lack of taste in decoration owing to the facto of course he'd had no - professional training or acad
emic training in that respect. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 Yes, oh yes, he'd be a professional baker be - besides being - besides being - baking bread - where he worked at Tase Green and Sons, Burslem. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 He - he also used to do all the - bake the slab cakes and things like that for them. So that he could - he could - do the confectionery too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother ever make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Yes. When - plums and damsons were in season, yes, she used to make her own jams. In fact - as far as I can remember - very few jams were bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about bottling fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
And bottling fruit, yes, she did a lot of that. They used to have the old Kilner jars, you know, the ones with screw tops. And, she would - she would bake - she would bottle quite a lot of fruit in season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 She has done pickles too, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did she ever make wine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 After I was married she made some rhubarb wine. And - I can always remember it, we were living in Seafield at that time, and - one }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 exploded}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  in the pantry and - it's a g
ood job there was nobody there when it exploded because it was - everything was fragmented, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But you can't remember her making wine when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not as a regular - not as a regular occupation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about family medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well family medicines - my father - was - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 great}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  believer in senna tea. Yes, senna tea was a regular with me father. If your stomach was out of order, camomile tea. And - yes, and my father was a great believer in Epsom Salts and lemon }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 . In fact, for donkey's years, every morning he took an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 egg cupful}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 of salts and lemon as he called it. For donkey's years - and he was as thin as a rake, and yet he would persist in taking this stuff. But senna tea, camomile tea. Well he lived long enough didn't he. Yes
. And he only died because he fell down and broke his thigh. Yes. Yes. Yes. Ninety-three. Ninety - ninety-two, nearly ninety-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about beer, did they ever brew beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 My father - no, because me father - I can say this quite honestly, me f
ather was a teetotaler until he was over seventy. Me mother used occasionally to have a half a pint which was fetched from the off licence by me very often and she would have that - no more than once a month, one half pint. Me father rather looked down up
o
n such pleasures as contrary to his religion - his religious beliefs. He never drank beer in his life. He started to drink wine - and a drop of brandy, but he must have been well over seventy by then. He never went into a picture house until - yes, he nev
er went into a picture house until he was - oh he would be a - be in his seventies. And he's never been in a theatre in his life. To him, those things were things of the devil. And as for cards in the house, he wouldn't - he wouldn't have them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You say he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 non}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 -conformist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 He was a non-conformist. He was a Methodist, yes. Yes. His church was his only other outside interest apart from his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember your parents growing any of their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 We never had an allotment.
 Me father started gardening - after he'd retired. He was seventy. And he became quite a - a decent gardener, that's when he learnt to garden, after he'd retired. He'd never had any time for it before. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So they would buy their vegetables and fruit would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 They'd have to, yes. Generally from the - the itinerant - greengrocer who came round two or three times a week with his horse and cart.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever keep }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I remember having a - a rabbit when I was a youngster 
and I remember a neighbour's dog came in and killed it and I was most upset about it. We had a dog for a while. But those are the only two - pets I can remember when I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 No food produc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 ing stock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh by no means, no. We hadn't any - no we'd no room for - no room for such things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember how many times a week you would eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - I would say most days of the week - when we didn't perhaps - we might have fish occasionally you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever get extra meat such as rabbit from poachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. No. No, the only meat that was bought - we come to rabbits those were bought out of Hanley market.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Apparently at that time poaching was rife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - to those - it would be. For those on the outskirts of the city where the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You were rather in the middle of the city?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. You see. Yes. Yes. Just below Cobridge cricket ground, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so that the rest of the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I would say
 occasionally yes, if - if her budget only allowed for - so much. Her portion might be smaller and probably her excuse would be that she wasn't over hungry, yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would the whole family benefit from your mother eating less or would it be just your father who would benefit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
That I couldn't say. I would say that me father's portion was. You see, they were brought up in a - a Victorian atmosphere and to a large extent that Victorian atmosphere persisted to our own household you see, so - that's as far as I could go on that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh I suppose so, yes. I wouldn't say that - I wouldn't say there was absolute silence at the dinner table, on the other hand - especially at the weekend, we were more or less subservient to my father's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 presence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or would you have to have a bit of everything? Or would you have to eat what was put in front of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well more or less we had to eat what was put in front of us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What was your parents attitude if you left something uneaten on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well we didn't have any - anything - anything to substitute for it. We either had it or we didn't and that was the end of it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh we could ask for it to be passed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 If - if there was any left, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You didn't feel you had to wait for it to be offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you expected to hold your cutlery in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In the normal way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, to - to - observe the usual table manner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Could you bring books or toys to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh no, no. When we sat at the table it was a matter of sitting there for a purpose. And your books - and - my father was very strict on that - in that respect, that you - you left your books and your toys - until after you'd finished your meal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well I - I would say that we - we - we had to - to ask permission to leave. We just didn't just finish and get up and fly out as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would you have to wait until everyone had finished or would you ask to be excused when you personally were finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well I - I couldn't tell - I couldn't remember those things, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well - let us remember this, that more or less we only all at the table, more or less, at the weekend when my father was not at work, otherwise it was a - a matriarchal family during the - during the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 At the weekend when your father was at home would you all sit down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Yes. Yes. Always at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you always sit in the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 More or less I should imagine, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember how the meal was served, by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh mother would do the serving, y
es. She would cook it and she would serve it. And she would clear away, I - I suppose when my sister grew up she would help with the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would there be any order of serving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I suppose father would come first. Then as to regard what order the others were served I wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember sitting anywhere else except at table, you were the youngest in your family weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember sitting anywhere else except at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 Well,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  I - I don't think, we may h
ave had one of those old high chairs you know, with a little table in front - but I can't remember it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh mother - mother, yes, yes, you could talk to me mother, yes. Me father - he was somewhat aloof.
 As I say, his only interests were work - and church. And therefore - he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 somewhat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 - Victorian in his attitude to us and in our attitude to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was your mother affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. She always put us - her children first and - s
he would see that they were well dressed even before she - thought about herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 If you had any worries of any sort could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Ordinary childish troubles, yes, I suppose so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Your father wasn't a particularly easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No. No, I don't think he ever got into a - a child's mind. As I say - he was obsessed with this idea of - work, he was over conscientious in that respect with regard to work and - his religious beliefs were such - he was a f
undamentalist you see and even to the day he died he believed in the - the actual word of the Bible you see. I know when I grew up and went to college and came back with a - a wider view of the world we had many and many an argument. Because he still - st
ill stuck to his old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 Victorian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 ideas on religion and I - I just couldn't wear them you see. When it come to Sunday, Sunday was a - a miserable day. We were dressed up in our Sunday bests. We're not supposed to kick a ball about. If me father had had his way
, even when I was grown up, I would never have read anything except something with religious flavour you see. The only periodicals that came into the house were - religious in flavour. There was the old Sunday Companion. I don't know whether anybody's men
t
ioned that to you before. It was a weekly paper but it was - it was - non-conformist in its attitude and it reminds in some respects of the present War Cry that the Salvation Army - dish out each week you see. That was the only - the only periodical that 
came into the house. It was religious. When we read other books there was - they were supposed to be taboo on Sunday. And as for playing games and cards and things like that, they were the works of the devil in me father's eyes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You wouldn't say your father was an affectionate man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No, no, no. He wasn't one who wanted to spend his time with his children. A matter of fact - I would say - no disrespect to the old fellow - that - well - he looked after us, he fed us and he clothed us. But h
e - he was never a pal in that respect. Yes, the old Victorian attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 They couldn't go to their parents with troubles in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not to the same extent that children do today, no. Yes, they were born and bred in Victorian times you see a
nd it was only what - it was only when the - the outbreak of the first world war that those old ideas began tom-disintegrate you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh with - we were supposed to speak to them - quite pro
perly and to behave to them - again - in the Victorian way. They were the parents, they were the father and mother, we were the children and there was a - a certain attitude that the children should - adopt towards their parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did they bring you up to behave in a particular way to your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh yes, we were supposed to - to behave when we did have little scraps among ourselves of course, the one in the wrong was - was ticked off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  attitude if you were hurt by another child, were you taught to hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh yes, we were taught to look after ourselves as though on occasions I remember my father - if a - bigger boys had been - troubling, I - I - on occasions I've known my father if he was available at the time take my side. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you know what kind of people your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh well me mother especially, me mother always had the idea that I should go into a profession and not work with me hands. You see. Now 
me - me - elder brother - he - he preferred to work with his hands you see, but I preferred to work with me head. and me mother always - in fact she sacrificed in order that she should - it was, she sacrificed and - and she financed me through - through c
o
llege you see. Those were the days when there were no grants from educations authorities you see. So that my two years in college down Cheltenham were financed solely out of my mother's savings. And she saved from what she saved from my father's earnings.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So it must have been a sacrifice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
It was, yes, yes. In fact she - she - she got into the attitude, as a good many people I know today, they - they were brought up - in - circumstances of penury you see. Although they looked after us as well as t
hey could according to their financial status - they always believed in putting a bit by for a rainy day and - they never got out of that attitude, where my mother was far better off in later life she couldn't bring herself to spend - money - that wasn't 
a
bsolutely necessary. Yes. It's the habit of years, you can't - you can't throw over any - in your - your - your later life, it's there. I know certain people now even in my profession, I can think of one in particular who came from very humble beginnings 
and has - had that attitude in life, never spend if you don't need to and now he's well off, he - he's - he's still - and he'll die leaving a lot of money to his children who'll simply - get rid of it as fast as it comes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh yes, we all used to - we were always - admonished to behave ourselves, to believe in God and to go to church regularly, in fact as I mentioned before, Sundays were the most dismal - miserable day
 of the week, Sunday school in the morning, Sunday school in the afternoon. And church at night. And - no - reading other than religious stuff, no games to be played. So for a - a growing lad, a lad in his teens it was a misery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did your father think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh he wouldn't hear of it. His son I must confess does occasionally come out with bad language when he's annoyed but me father - I think the - the worst word I ever heard him use was the word dash. Yes. And that was - that's as near
 to swearing as he ever go, yes. No, he was very - and for the word of Jesus to be taken in vain, Christ or anything like that, to him was a - was a - a very great sin. He never swore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No,
 I wouldn't say so, not on - on - on equal terms. There was still this somewhat Victorian attitude that children would be seen and not heard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you punished if you did something your parents disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 Undoubtedly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 By - physically, oh yes, physically as well as perhaps - by being deprived of something. No doubt about it, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You were punished physically?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well we were probably slapped - probably slapped across the behind, oh yes, we were punished phys
ically. But never brutally, put it that way, never brutally but we were certainly punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 By whom?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well it would depend upon who saw it, whether it was mother or father. Mother would - would punish with perhaps a slap. My father would punish with - perhaps a slap or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. I don't think so. Nothing stand out in my mind after all these years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember how you felt when punishment was being doled out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, no lasting impression, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would you say you received your ideas on how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh undoubtedly, yes, they set a standard that we were supposed to conform to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was this both parents or one in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh both parents but - I suppose that - mother being - like all women with their children would perhaps be a little more lenient }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 than}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  me father who was - somewhat of a - in respect of behaviour - somewhat of a martinet you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 If you had a birthday would it be any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - very little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 different}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  actually. Finances were not - too great. There's be a - a present. We might have a - an extra - fuss at teatime, something like that, but there was nothing 
out of the ordinary, there were no great celebrations for any of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But you did know it was your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember anything out of the ordinary that you did with your parents on Christmas Day, how would that differ from a normal day?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I should say - it was a kind of a - a highlight in the - the year's activities, Christmas Day dawned, presents at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 breakfast time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 , playing with the presents. The usual - Christmas dinner and Christmas tea, it was perhaps - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 family wise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  the highlight of the - of the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever have any musical instruments in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 home}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 My father was very fond of the old harmonium. I fiddled quite a bit on it. Later when the - my sister grew up we had a piano as well.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No, no, my father's music - musical activities consisted of - playing - hymns. Mostly the old Sankey variety if you remember them. Oh well, Sankey and - there used to be a book - Sankey and - Sankey and - what wa
s the other name. Anyhow - they were - largely sung at that time to the end of the 19}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  century, beginning of the 20}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 century, in - non-conformist homes. Hymns like The Old Rugged Cross and things like that. Do you know it? Well that came out of the old Sankey - Sankey and Moodie the name of it was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you sing with your father, did you ever all sing together while he played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh very seldom. Very seldom. No, my father was - family wise somewhat of a - shall we say - far removed, possibly d
ue to the fact that his activities were work and church and he'd very little time for anything else so - there were very little time for - taking much interest in the children as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did anyone in the family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 My mother'd got quite a good voice and she - her vocabulary was limited to most of these old - hymn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7958857\charrsid15484224 tunes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
. And perhaps one or two of the - popular tuneful melodies of that day. My sister, when she grew up, she joined - as I did later, for a while, the - the Stoke on Trent choral society. And I have sung in the Dream of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Olwen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
he Messiah on several occasions. It was one of the leading societies of North Staffordshire at that time, yes. From it has developed I think more or less by process of am}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
algamation the present Ceramic C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 hoir. It is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No - occasionally - I've got - a faint recollection of playing what was called lotto in those days. Lotto of course is - was the forerunner of the present bingo, you see. It was referred to in the Army as housey-housey, that's right. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Only - well - prizes that we used to get - every year from - for regular attendance at Sunday school. And - the rest were - religious books that me father may have - accumulated over the years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well I don't ever remember a daily newspaper coming into the house. As I told you about magazines, they - the Sunday Companion was a regular - periodical. But I don't think that we ever had a regular daily or evening newspaper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember your father or mother reading very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 My father would read a lot but as I say - his reading was - religious in tone. My mother would read - the Sunday Companion. Mu
ch lighter reading. Occasionally she would read a - she would read a - a novel of the type that was - popular in those days, the kind of - East }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Lynn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  and things like that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 type}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  of novel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did they ever read aloud to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. I don't think so. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family while you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 I have very, very faint recollections of me mother's mother - that is my maternal grandmother's funeral. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And that would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would you have attended it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh - 
I suppose all the - the near family relations, that would be somewhere in the region of what - before the last word - before the first world war. I should only be seven or eight or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I probably went to the house
, you know, but I - I don't think I attended the funeral in church or the ceremonies at the graveside, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would the family wear mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, in those days it was - it was - the accepted thing that once there was a - a
 bereavement in the family you hurried of to the - either to the - dressmaker's or to the - or to the tailors and you adorned yourself in black. And that possibly last for - a month or so. Yes, for close relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you ever taken out visiting friends, relations or neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well, the only - perhaps - I won't say regular, but the only visits we made were to me father's brother in - who lived in Longton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Who would take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - probably both mother and father would go with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh only with mother - if she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 wanted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  to - to buy us some clothes, shoes or - a suit or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I can't ever recollect in my young life ever going out with me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember any outings, any sort of special outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh well - later on when I was about ten or eleven we managed tom- we managed to have a week's holiday in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would this be on a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
On the Bank Holiday. And that was in reasonable distance of the Potteries and we used to go out in - the old - we used to hire a - an old - brake, do you remember the - have you ever seen one of those, oh well it was a - drawn by two horses. It was a kind
 
of open wagonette with - seats round the sides. I suppose - when the motor came into - into being - the open charabanc would - would have taken its place. But it would hold about I should say - a dozen people you see, seated on seats. It was a kind of an 
open - after the style of an open dray with sides to and - rows of seats on, we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No cover?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, no cover, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How many of you would go on this holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh well, just the family went. My mother, father, my - me brothers, that wo
uld be - and a sister possibly. About five or six I think, yes. We - we've been to - we had a holiday at - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Naughton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
-in-Hales, near to Market Drayton, that was one. We had another one near to Ecclesham, a little place called Knighton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What sort of place would you stay at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 It was at mostly farm house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you enjoy this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh yes. They were - I've still vivid recollections of the - the little happenings that - that occurred there because - I was always fond of the country, I still am you s
ee, and - farm life has always interested me and even now I can talk to a farmer although I've had no experience of farming but - its way and things connected with the farm always interest me. His crops and his animals and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What were these happenings on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well when we were staying at Knighton, not far away, it's round in the Ecclesham district there, there was an old - Manor House called Ranton Abbey. And we - we walked there, it was only two or three miles. I remember crossing a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 field}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 towards the Abbey and I - I've never seen so many rabbits in the field, it was - there must have been thousands of them, and of course as we cross the field they - they scurried away. But I've never seen so many wild rabbits congregated toge
ther in all my life. And - Ranton Abby's now burned down, it was burned down a few years ago. But there was a nice big lake there that held pike. Remember the gamekeeper or somebody telling us that these pike had been known to drag swans underneath you se
e
. Yes. Now - with - the same time, when we were there - the war broke out. The first world war that is, on August the fourth wasn't it - 19 - 1914. Yes. And my brother went in the Army, that is my step-brother, the eldest of the family, he was there with 
us at the time. I've recollection of Naughton-in-Hales which is near to Market Drayton. There's the - on a farm, killing a sheep on the bench by the old fashioned method of holding it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
down and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  slitting it's throat, and that has never - left my mind at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Didn't you find it rather }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 gory}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
I did, I - it rather - rather upsetting for a child to see it - yes. Yes. Of course farmers in those days were rough and ready, they wanted some - some mutton so they just - put a sheep on a - on a saw bench, hold
 it down and slit its throat and I can always remember the - the scene. And after that I remember I passed an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 abattoir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 as a matter of fact, as a matter of fact coming to the office this morning I was behind a lorry that turned into the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 abattoir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  in Hanley there and - and I thought - immediately thought of the expectation of life of the animals inside you see. I must confess that if I had to kill me own meat I should be vegetarian. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever go to the sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. First - visit to th
e sea. I should be eleven I think and we went to New Brighton for a week. That was my first view of the sea and it wasn't real sea, it was the Mersey wasn't it. But that was my first visit to the seaside and we stayed a week there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Play on the sands, I remember my brother - we had a toy each, my brother had one of these - mechanical tin submarines that he used to sail in the - in the ponds on the beach. That was my first visit to the seaside. I was eleven then, yes. Oh yes,
 and my brother would be about - my brother would be about fourteen. That was his first visit to the seaside, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So that would be an occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh it was, yes. It was at - at New Brighton, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Now we'll talk about weekends and religion,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh dear, the worst - the worst time of the week. When Sunday came - Saturday was all right but when Sunday came we were dressed in our best - we were not supposed to - partake of any of the ordinary weekday activities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother and father think it wrong to work or play games on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
That's right. It was in my father's point of view wrong to work and play or even read anything that hadn't got a religious slant to it. Coupled with that - Sunday school in the morning, Sunday school 
in the afternoon and chapel at night, which were absolutely - contrary to what - a - a normal lad's - wants in those days you see. So that - I was always glad when Sunday was over and the - the weekday started again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What denomination did you say your father was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was your mother a Methodist also?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did she practice, did she go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh she went regularly every Sunday evening with me father to chapel, oh yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever go to chapel together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, we always went together as a family at night. And my father of course was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  of the Sunday school so - we had to set an example and go with him you see. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever go to any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh yes, there was the usual treats you know. And they would he taken - either by train or - mostly by train to places, within a reasonable distance of the potteries. I think we went to Rudges once, we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 certainly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  went to Me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
ford once, tha
t's Barlaston you see. But never far afield, it would be perhaps an hour's journey or less than that in those days. We would have hired a field. There were games and prizes. And there was a - a kind of alfresco tea, you see, a big urn was taken out and te
a made. The - the food would have been provided by the - the women helpers of the church you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you enjoy those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, those were looked forward to because - to leave home for the afternoon or the day and go out into the country in those
 days was - was quite an occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you take part in any other social activities organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I joined the choir at quite an early age. I became - for a while - a Sunday school teacher and then for a while the - the secretary of t
he Sunday - of the Sunday school. But those activities finished when I went to college and I came back with a - you might say a broadened outlook, a very different outlook indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What was your father's reaction to your changed attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh we h
ad many and many a violent argument on it. He persisting in his old fundamental ideas and - on my part, trying to - to give him some idea of the - of my ideas on religion in the light of modern knowledge. But he - he simply wouldn't swallow it. Anything t
hat ran contrary to the word in the Bible - was anathema to him. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 And so that for many, many years we were not the best of friends.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You became friendly later didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, when he - when he mellowed somewhat and he realized that I'd gone my 
way and he persisted in his that - I think more or less that he accepted the fact that - oil and water wouldn't quite mix.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you belong to any club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Oh they used to have a youth - a kind - well first of all there was a 
Band of Hope, that was very, very non-conformist, where you signed the - what do they call it - yes, well they were - they were - they were - they were organisations - fostered by the - by the non-conformist fraternity to whom alcohol in any form was an e
vil to be shunned. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Something after the style of the Salvation Army you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did they have a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well that was it, the Band of Hope was the temperance - that was the temperance club. And then a bit later on they did have a kind of a -
 a kind of a youth club to keep the youngsters together one night a week but there were the only the - what I might call the - the old fashioned childish games. Spinning the - the tray and rushing to catch it before it fell down. Nothing approximating to 
the modern youth club. It was just something to keep you off the streets and - perhaps in those days in the light of the attitude of grown ups to youngsters it was something to the good but in time it began to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 pall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  because the activities were - well they we
ren't in keeping with the - a normal - teenagers - desire for - for seeing life and - like that, yes. It was - it was - more or less a - a youth club run on adult ideas.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was grace said at meals in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Always. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 My father was very, very pa
rticular that you said grace before any meal, even to the day he died. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Never altered, although we - more or less - grew out of the habit, he always persisted in it. And at - on Sunday meals we could never start until we all sat down to table together and he said grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you taught to pray at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Yes. I must confess that I haven't got out of the habit now. I sometimes wonder in the light of modern knowledge - and I thought a lot about - orthodox religion and - I'm - I'm convinced that - the
re is a lot in orthodox religion which is not religion at all. It's only habit that has grown up over the ages. And I think that - space age discovery and things like that are going to have a profound affect upon - upon our attitude to religion. We still 
p
ersist in religion although we say God is a spirit, we still persist in identifying him with a human being don't we. And we still persist in going to church and praising his name and if he's - if he's a spirit beyond - well omnipotent and everything like 
that he doesn't want us singing his praises. My belief that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 religion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 is basically your attitudes - the right attitude to your neighbour. You see. And when you think of some of these ridiculous practices that exist in various - religions throughout the world
 - I cannot identity them with real - with religion as I understand it. You - well you - you get - for instance you get the - you get the - the Rabbi in the Jewish church - using in human methods to - to slaughter the kosher meat. Ah well, you know that n
o orthodox Jew will eat meat without it is what you call kosher meat. Now kosher meat - every Friday morning I believe, down to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 abattoir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  goes the - the Rabbi and one beast is selected. Now you know in the modern }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 abattoir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 everything is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 done}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  humanely. Not
 so with the - with the Kosher. With the Rabbi. The beast is standing there and he's got a huge curved knife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do they still do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Aye. Yes. And he simply slits its }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 throat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 . Nearly cuts its head off - with one blow. That is because - if you rea
d the book of Genesis and the book of Exodus and all that - it was laid down by Moses and they still persist in it. And when the humane act was brought in with regard to - a few years ago with regard to slaughtering of animals in this country - there was 
p
rovision made - that the Jewish people should be allowed to slaughter their meat in their own time honoured way. Well of course it would - it would have upset the Jewish community and they still are allowed to slaughter their meat according to the Biblica
l
 directions. And what has that got to do with religion, I don't know. You see. And you've got the same peculiar ideas throughout all the religions of the world. Which are buried in the past you see, and are traditional and you know how hard it is to break
 tradition.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh yes. Yes. At - probably on Sunday nights. Especially when we were very young, yes. As I say, Sunday was - that was the only time when father was a member of the family you might put it you see. And - t
herefore - there were family prayers at night - on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Very - very little, except when election time came round and - he was - and mother was of course I suppose - to some 
extent, it might have flavoured our young outlook on politics - they were Liberals. That was before the - birth of the Labour party. So they were Liberals. Well you see, you don't know - you don't know how you've lived do you? Well you see the Labour part
y didn't really come into being until the late 1920's did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 father was Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was your mother also Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well, yes, yes, oh yes. There were no arguments about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you know why they held those views particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well the Conservatives in that - in those days, still going by the - the old name of the Tories, were supposed to - to favour - taxes - import taxes and things like that. Whereas the Liberals were advocating free trade you see. And the arguments w
ere that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Tory}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 policy of - tariffs you see - kept up the price of food and things like that whereas the Liberals, their man platform was what was called Tariff Reform. Which was free trade you see. And - those were the main arguments in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember your parents voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh they would go. They would go to - to register their votes, yes. They would certainly vote Liberal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their job
 or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you feel that father was under any pressure of this kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. No, I don't think so. I've never - I never had any occasion to - to dream that he - that - his work - in any way influenc
ed his - his voting freedom. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was your father a member of the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did he work for the party at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, he hadn't no connections - as I've told you, his only connections - close connections with anything were his work and his church.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So the only political occurrence would be election time would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And the same applied to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Oh yes. Well of course mother was like many housewives in those days. She was tied to the house and the family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you think your father would have influenced your mother in her views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not necessarily, no, because - because mother had a - had a mind of her own when it - and she would on occasions - be diametri
cally opposed to me father. And I don't think she would go his way just because he said so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your parents have any interests outside the home other than religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. I just - I can remember when I was in my - early teens, perhaps in the lat
e - eight - nine - onwards - they had a bike each. And they used to go out on Saturday afternoons. And we were left to our own devices and they would go out for an afternoon run and come back shall we say - seven or eight o'clock at night in the summer, a
nd they had a bike each and - for - places within easy reach you see. See the motor car then was only in its infancy. And only those with money could afford a car you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
And they had a bike and they - for many, many years they - they regularly - had these Saturday afternoon excursions.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Your father worked mostly nights so would he never sort of have evenings at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Well, for many, many years he - as I say, he worked nights, so that would mean he would go on duty about eight or nine o'clock at 
night, he'd be home about six the next morning. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
He'd have his breakfast and go to bed and probably sleep until about - four or five o'clock in the afternoon and then - he'd have no time before he went to work. Later on in life, night work was more or less 
abolished but - he had to start work very early in the morning, and being a foreman baker her had to see to all the mixing of the - the dough so that very often he was rising about half past four or five in the morning, walking to work, which would be - a
 two mile walk, and getting there about half past five to six you see. And preparing things for when the ordinary bakers came in about half past six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 A very responsible position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, yes. On - he was responsible for the - the quality of the - the stuff turned out of the baker. And - and everything else you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember your mother going out by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh only - the occasion must have been few and far between, she may have gone to visit some close relation }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 within}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  - what - a mile - two miles of the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But this wasn't very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your father ever go to any pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. He's never been in a pub in his life. Never been in a pub in his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 He only started drinking wine when he was quite old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did he belong to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did he take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. None whatsoever. Not a sporting type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember your parents belonging to any savings clubs, boot clubs, sick clubs, funeral clubs and the like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I've got an idea at one time - they - they had these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Provident}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  cheques. Now they still exist - in existence today aren't they. And probably mother did that to - save a little each week in order to buy our - our charity - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Your anniversary clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 They used to be referred to as the charity. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 My sister I was fond of. Me - the immediately - immediate elder brother, who's still living, we got on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Is this the brother that didn't live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No, no, no, this is the brother who still lives in Sneyd Green. He lives less than a mile away from me and I haven't seen him for about three years. We've never had anything in common. 
He was not sporting inclined. I was. He was very mechanically minded. Was always making little things. I was out playing. We never had anything in common really. We were never brothers in the proper sense of the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 When you played out who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 My immediate neighbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was this a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, he was a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh in the - there was quite a - there was quite a - an expanse of - rough land just behind the house, and we used to play there, we mad
e up our own games. We played cricket and football. Marbles. Cigarette cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you allowed to get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I very often came in dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother object?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - very often what used to happen, we used to - go out in - put on pe
rhaps older pairs of shoes and things like that you see, in order to play. Oh yes, we came home - dirty enough at times and we thoroughly enjoyed it. Probably the dirtier we got the - the happier we were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you allowed to play with anyone you pleased or were you discouraged from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
I wouldn't say we were ever discouraged with playing with certain children because most of the children in the immediate neighbourhood with whom we played were more or less of the same social group. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have any particular hobbies while you were a youngster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 A youngster? No, not particular. Very liberal as my likes and dislikes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Only once I kept a rabbit and the neighbour's dog killed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. Only cigarette cards and marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have a good collection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, well of course we used to - we used to play against one another and - we either lost them or won you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
We hadn't a garden. At that time, no. My own garden - my first gardening experience, I was still in the - what was called the elementary school then, Graville, in Newhawker
 Road - Cobridge and - the war had just started and - there was - the growth of the allotments you know to grow your own food, I remember there the - head park keeper from - Burslem Park used to come once a week to school and after school hours, half past
 four, behind the school we had a - an allotment and he taught us how to grow - vegetables and how to keep allotments. And it was from then that my - I should think my interest in gardening started you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Only once. I've ofte
n thought I'd like to become a fisherman, but I've never had the time and the opportunity. Once I remember going fishing, I must have been - perhaps thirteen or fourteen. We cycled somewhere towards }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 Wellington}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  and fished in a little pond. I hadn't any prop
er fishing tackle. And I know we had a whole host of little perch I think they were about two inches long. That was the only excursion I had - fishing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you walk very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, because - occasionally we might have had - on a nice day during
 the holiday we might have - perhaps gone as far as Melton or Trenton. But we had to walk both ways. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I had a bike later on in life, a secondhand bike and - I remember once we went to - one holiday time, me and 
me brother, and we cycled round - Hendon and Brownhedge. And - we probably had although I may have forgot - I've probably forgotten now - various other little excursions of - several miles out into the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You said you were rather keen on sports or you were inclined this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Yes, well - later on in life, when I was about seven - sixteen or seventeen, at the church we ran the - a football club and we joined what was called the Country Minor League then. I was a member of that team. We had to
 - provide sixpence a week out of our own pocket to pay }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 expenses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
, to buy footballs, strip and - pay the referee's expenses. Pay for the hire of the ground. That sixpence a week used to take, what, at least fifty percent of me pocket money, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you have any interest in other sports, before this started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well only - only in so much as we used to play cricket and things like that on the spare ground opposite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  - perhaps - homemade bats and a very rough and bumpy pitch, where you took you
r life in your hands. And - probably kicking about a football. Yes. Kicking about a football among - scrap sides of five or six a side that used to get together. But the only organised sport I took part in, prior to going to college, of course, as I say -
 joining this - this - this - chapel team.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Theatre was frowned upon by my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Now the cinema, let me see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes, I used to go to the - the cinema. There w
as one which is now the Roman Catholic church hall at the top of Cobridge, what was it called. Victoria, something like that. The end of Grange Street in Cobridge. The building is still there. We used to go on a Saturday afternoon, it cost us about a penn
y or tuppence. I remember seeing the Great Train }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Robbery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 . And - these early comedies and Charlie Chaplin films.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever go to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, no. Those things were frowned upon by my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, that's the only way - the only place where pocket money came from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember how much you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 It was very little, it was only a few coppers a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 This was regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes, it was regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh well - it'd be on sweets. Perhaps buying marbles. And probably - a visit to the pictures and that was - more or less sewed up the whole lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house and family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
I've got an idea that for a while later on in life my mother's sister, who was a spinster, she died a spinster, came to live with us for a while. So she would help, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 If your mother was ill or confined to bed for any reason how would she manage, w
hen one of the younger children were born how would she cope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - I wouldn't know because I am the youngest so I wouldn't know would I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember your mother ever being ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not - not - she was a very healthy woman. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 So very, very
 seldom was she - incapacitated in that respect.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You said your parents had relations living nearby, did they see them very often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not particularly, no. Might perhaps once a week a something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did they have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, no. They were very - no, she never made friends with neighbours or visited one - neighbours houses or things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Apart from - acquaintances you might call them - who were connected with the church and whom she met at the meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would she ever go visiting these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Very very seldom if any - no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 Very, very seldom if any.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did anyone ever call to your house sort of casually without an invitation, friends or relations or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 The occasion must have been so infrequent that I - I've no recollection of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In that time before 1918 can you tell me what groups you thought society was divided into, how many social classes were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I should say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And to which one you thought you particularly belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
I would say - the very highest class of all, Royalty and peerages and things like that. Then the - the people with plenty of money, approximating to the successful businessman today. Then th
e ordinary working man, like my father. And then possibly the other class who lived in the - in what we should term today the slums. The - the drunkards and the - the down and outs. The ragged people and things like that. I would say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What would be your term for that particular class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I don't know we had any particular term for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But you considered yourself the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Just the slight above them. We were - if there were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224  four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  classes of society, the - Royalty and - the title and the - the very successful businessman, then the ordinary working class and then - the very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 ,
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  very poor class. And I should say we were in the - we were in the - the second state. We weren't the very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  very poor.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So there was the poor class and the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 The successful businessman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would that be the middle class would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh no. That would be the upper middle class and we were probably the lower middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What were the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 peerage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  and the really wealthy people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh well, they were - what would - I don't know how you would - you would term them. You'd call them the peerage I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But you would have divided society into four classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 There were round about four classes at that time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And you belonged to the lower middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Lower middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well the same people who -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Having what sort of occupations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - ordinary artisan occupations. There wa
s a neighbour - next door neighbour who - who's son I used to play very often with, he worked at the nearby racecourse colliery. He was the - the bank foreman. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
And there was - another neighbour who was a - a modeller on a - a potworks. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Ordinary everyday occupations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In the other classes that you've talked about, what sort of people would belong to the lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well the type of people you'd see - and it was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 common}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  in those days - in - the colliers, they would come home from work, there we
re no pit baths or anything like that. And they would come home in their dirt, they would have their meals and they would sit on their doorstep in their dirt in summer, perhaps at night you would see them - the ladies - the women of the family, sitting on
 the doorstep with a jog of beer by their side you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 This was a regular }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 occurrence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, in the - among - in the - in the poorer streets, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What sort of people would belong to the upper middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well people like -
 people like ourselves who would - who would never go out without they - they were dressed up. Were never - take part in street brawls or things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What sort of occupations would the upper middle class have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - mush the s
ame occupation. They would have - ordinary jobs. Some of them would only be - more or less the - more or less - you would - you would class your father -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, I wouldn't say so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you ever told to show respect in some way to any person particularly or to touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, we were always taught I suppose - partly from home and partly from school, that people like teachers and he
admasters and - should always be treated with respect. Such as raising the cap and things like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was there anyone other than your schoolmasters that you would call sir or any lady that would call madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well I don't know as a youngster 
whether I ever came - into much contact with those type of people outside - outside school. So there was really very little or no occasion on which it was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 In your particular district who were considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well just below us lived a - an Inspector of the Police, he was treated with some deference. But otherwise - in the immediate neighbourhood we were more or less of the - the same social standing and so - neither one or the other was more important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Who would you suppose the clergy associated with, what sort of people would the clergy be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well actually, coming from a non-conformist home and going to - a non-conformist chapel it was only on rare occasions during the twelve months that someone in Holy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 O}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 rders came to - came to preach and mostly the Sunday services were taken by lay preachers who were - who were only ordinary everyday working class people you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Who would teachers associate with, what sort of people would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You m
ean the - teachers who were teaching us as a - as - as a vocation. Well - in those days or today? In those days? I wouldn't know. Because I was only a - a - a boy and they were - more or less - well, I suppose I considered them - belonging to an upper hie
rarchy you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What about employers, farmers and those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 sorts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  of people, would you have anything particular to say about those types?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well my father's original employer, he worked for Chase Green and Sons, greengrocers - not greengrocers - g
rocers, dry salters and bakers, and the old man with home he had most association, it was more or less on the old kind of family business basis where workmen were more - more or less considered as - as part of the undertaking. Later when the - the old man
 
- went out of the business, his son took over, then there crept in between me father and the son - a different attitude. Whereas the son wanted - was more or less inclined to say, I'm the boss, you're the workmen, it got rid of that relationship that had 
p
reviously existed you see and - it led to - to a series of disputes, which in the end I suppose culminated with my father - leaving the - leaving the - the business and going into - at the insurance business. But they never hit it off, it's quite - it's p
o
ssibly certain that my father and the son - who took over the business - never really hit it off. My father was somewhat of a stubborn kind of man, once he'd set his mind on a certain course of action nothing would shake him and I suppose the son was not 
going to be in a way dictated to by a workman and it led to - this - well - an unfriendly atmosphere shall we put it that way, which sooner or later was bound to be resolved in - one of them leaving, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would you say the people who went to chapel were made of people largely like yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would you have any comments to make about people who went to church? What sort of people they were likely to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well - actually you see the - the friend I used to play with was a Roma
n Catholic Now of course I'd been brought up to consider - not so much so much by teaching from my parents but from the general attitude of one religious sect to another that - on the religious side they were - they were not to be - associated with. Apart
 
from religion we used to get on very well but on the religious side well of course among - as children playing - it was - it was never - broached and - in those days religion was in - in these - very tight compartments and non-conformists had very little 
to do with the - the church of England or with the Roman Catholics and that went for everyone you see. That what you did on Sundays was - something - entirely your own business and nothing to do with - yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where you lived did all the people in t
he working class, your own class, have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within that same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I would say - in the - immediate district in which we lived we were all more or less of the - the same social stan
ding. There was no - no one outstanding shall we say with - with more money and more of the worldly goods than the other which would lift them in to a - a higher status.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were there people who were perhaps worse off than yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well in the i
mmediate district there were none who were really worse off, no. Perhaps - a quarter of a mile away there was the - a - a lower working class district where the - the people were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 miners}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  and - what we did consider in those days of a lower status with which our district had very little in common you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you think you could describe a family in the middle class group, a family that you would see about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes, well I'm thinking of - I'm thinking of a - a family that was - connected with the - the c
hapel to which I went, they were builders. And therefore their financial background was - shall we say, much more healthy than ours was. Although we were on very friendly terms with them, there's no snobbishness whatsoever, but they lived - they lived - s
hall we say, on a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 slightly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 higher social plane, they had more money to spend. They could - gratify their - their wants - financially, whereas we had to - had to look after our coppers as it were from a family point of view. They were probably - although
 we were well dressed they were - better well dressed if you understand what I mean. Otherwise their - their interests more or less were - much the same as ours but - on a slightly higher social plane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Could you describe a family in the upper classes do you think, anyone about that you would consider to be really wealthy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No, I've never had any - as a child I had never any - connection with - with one of those families so that - I couldn't really - give you a - a description of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you think that any one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well I would say in those days that - although we know that money talks - even now, I would say that money there - did - more or less - demarcate the various classes. How much money you'
d got depended on - in what social circle you moved you see. There was - it was - you either stayed in the lower class and would never presume to gatecrash into the - into the - the class immediately above and like that, whereas today - although money sti
l
l does talk, there is less - less of this - social demarcation as there was in those days you see. I suppose it was - really a carry over from the old Victorian idea that - it was God's will that you were born into a certain class and there you stayed and
 you shouldn't presume to try and get out of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 some}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  families who where thought of as particularly rough and some that were thought of as particularly respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, when I mentioned a moment or two ago that about a quarter of 
a mile away there was a district where the - we considered that they were of a lower social status, well I'm thinking of a particular street called Rutland Street in Bootham, Hanley that is, and - if you lived in Rutland Street more or less it denoted - t
he social class to which you belonged you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
And they were rather rough and ready, they were inclined to - Saturday nights to - to be drink and street rows were very, very frequent you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
That was the accepted thing in that district whereas - it - it wasn't in our district our you see, and they - they - it kind of was an evidence of their - of their social standing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 So your area was more upper working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well certainly - yes, a sub division, a higher sub division of the working class }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 than}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  the one I've just mentioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember there being a distinction of any kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I would imagine, yes. I would imagine that - a man who was a craftsman, like me father was a baker and the other gentleman I ment
ioned some time ago who was a - a pottery modeler - they would be considered slightly superior by reason of the - the work they undertook to a man who was only - more or less a labourer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 your mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  and father having the same attitude to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
I would say yes, I - I would say along those lines it was - common that - the attitudes of - one group to another was a family attitude, not a personal attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you think that your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh yes, yes, I think both mother and father. Realized that - they were - in a certain social group and they never - as I - I mentioned before about old Victorian attitudes, they were born into a group, it was God's w
ill you should be there and more or less - that being so there was need to - to aspire to - join a higher group. A kind of Victorian attitude. It was - which actually creeps into them, before my time, I should say pre-1900, by the church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would you s
ay the reason for your mother's attitude was her parents or her work, your father, her home life, any particular reason at all, you say it was bred into them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well I think it was - it was - it - I think it was the thinking of the times. That you - mo
re or less - it was God's will that you were in this group or that group or the other group and that that being so - you accepted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another, do you think there was anyone who did change classes 
for any reason at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No, I can't remember any but I should imagine - that one of these go ahead boys who might have made money and - wanted to - by reason of his money to - seek entry into - into one of the upper classes would have found it somewha
t difficult - because the old Victorian attitude towards what we might call breeding, you see, money wasn't everything, you got to have a - a social background in keeping with your money you see. And for somebody to come from the lower stratum to a much h
igher stratum simply by reason of the - the money he had made was not so acceptable in those days as it might be today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember anyone in particular who would be described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Gentleman in what sense? You s
ee, there are two connotations of gentleman. A gentleman is - is a - is a man who - in its best sense - one, a man or a woman who - treats his fellows in - in a - what we might call a gentlemanly manner. But in the - in the period }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  which we're talking no
w - a gentleman in those days was a matter of a social status, you see what I mean, you see. And - where we say to - someone today, well he's a gentleman it has nothing to do with what he owns or - or how much money he's got. Yes. Whereas - there were ver
y few people that I can remember in - in those days who would - you would class as gentleman in the Victorian sense of the word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes, yes, policemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did you think of him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well the policemen in those days were somebody to be - to be feared. Once - what over you were doing, if a policeman walked round the corner you scarpered pretty fast - whether you were - up to - childish pranks or not, you just kept out of 
the way. He represented the law and the law meant something in those days - that it doesn't today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember your mother threatening you with, I'll fetch a policeman to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh it's quite possible, I can't remember anything - any specific incident, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How do you think policemen treated people, did you hear people say how they were treated by the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well actually in those days you kept away from the law as far as possible and I'd - I'd no recollection of any specific in
cident in which the police and any of my acquaintances were - were really involved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I can't remember who it was. Oh no, wait a minute, wait a minute, was our home rente
d. Let me see. This is in Cobridge Road. I've got an idea that was rented but when we left there and went to live in Sneyd Green in 1919 we bought that house and we - from that time onwards - we've been owner occupiers. I can't remember about the Cobridge
 Road house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember feeling that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 your parents}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well I won't say a struggle but I would say that it was - it wasn't easy. We've known of - or I did know of a - people who had a much harder struggle th
an we had but we'd never any money to spare - what the standard of life we achieved was only achieved by - by the - by being very - pennywise. We'd no money to throw away on - on frivolities. And therefore I suppose - we always looked at our pennies befor
e we - we spent them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did this have any sort of effect upon you as a child, did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 ell - yes, I - I used to be env}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 ious at times of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 children who got more money to spend than I had. We only had a few coppers a week pocket
 money and that had to last us from one week's end to the other, there was no going in the middle of the week to mother or me father for that matter, asking for - anything extra because we knew we wouldn't get it. I don't thin the family budget would allo
w it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember your father being ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Yes, well as I told you, I just - up 'til the time - what - when I was due to leave - Hanley High school, I just passed the Oxford Local, which is the - was the corresponding - exa
mination to the - General Certificate today - and I remember the headmaster of Hanley High School wanted me to go on to university. Me father had fallen out of work, he had this period about three months off with sciatica and one thing and another. And at
 the end of that period he was - he was - he lost his jobs as a - a baker. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
There was no social security and so things were very, very learn and I had to give up all thoughts of going on to university and - go straight away into the teaching profession you see, in order to relieve some of the - financial strain at home.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you remember the difference this period of unemployment made to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. No. No, we still - we still - we were still fed and clothed. But where - where the belt was drawn 
in I - I don't know. Probably my mother was the economist of the house. And she more or less dictated what would be spent and how it would be spent. And I suppose - she was responsible for the finances you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever have to get help from the guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
No. No, we - we would consider it a - oh it's very much infra dig for us to have to go on to - onto the parish as it was called in those days. No, we never at anytime - would rather have gone short rather than to seek their help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did going on to the parish mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well, people who were down and out could go on to - could apply for relief from the parish. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 It was looked upon as a hand out - from the authorities to the - the very, very poor people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And it was conside
red somewhat of a social stigma, you see. Whereas today, social security by 1 - is - well it is drilled into us these days that it is our right you see. But in those days it was a - it was a hand out, it was a charity you see, to which you went begging. Y
es. That's right, but it was considered a stigma in those days to have to go and - and ask for parish }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 relief}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  as we called it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you ever remember anyone in the district of whom people particularly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
disapproved}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not in our immediate district no. 
That other area - yes, there - there would be because they were - you see, bad language in those days was considered - something that shouldn't be used, it was a lowering of your status - whereas today of course bad language is - is part of common speech 
isn't it, what we would call bad language today. But in those days it was considered a - a kind of a - the use of bad language kind of denoted the stratum of society from which you came.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember anyone that was particularly rough or of wh
om people particularly disapproved, was there anyone way in which people showed their disapproval, do you remember stories of anyone being made to leave by rough music and the like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No. I would only say with those who were - we - we considered - of a
 lower social status, we were told more or less - not - not to play with them and things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents or a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No - I would say that - I was given lessons in music and - 
oh I'd be about thirteen or fourteen, I used to go out about once or twice a week to have lessons on - on the - on the - the old harmonium you see. That lasted for about what - twelve months or so then that was given up, I don't think for instance that - 
that would be somewhere about the time when we were in this - state of financial stringency and - I think it was given up by reason of that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 But not your actual school lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I should be - the very possible early state - four or five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 When you first started what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Half past nine. Used to come home, it was about what - quarter of a mile - home for midday meal. It was half
 past nine to half past twelve. Two o'clock to half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You went for the full day as soon as you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You didn't just go to morning school at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What we called
 an ordinary elementary school in those days. Divided into infants - and then - what we call the elementary - oh what was known as the elementary school, yes, and - in the - after you'd left the infants school you went into the upper school, and your prog
r
ess then was - well dependant upon your ability. If you couldn't - if you couldn't learn you stayed in the class from which - in which you - according to your - your ability, you see, some of the real - what we would class to day as D scholars - would sta
y
 in standard one or standard two - and perhaps leave in that standard you see. Whereas today you see, you - you are - you are taught in groups of - in - of the same age you see. Although you might - you might stream those groups, you say a group of - in a
 
big school - of - a group of thirteen year old scholars - might be grouped into three streams according to their ability you see and the age - the bright ones you might call A's would be put together, the not so bright, the B's and the - those who were - 
really not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 academically}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  minded at all and - couldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 assimilate
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  the abstract thoughts would - would go into C's and D's you see. But - in those days you simply you were - there were standards from one to ex seven and your progress up the school depended 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2700175\charrsid15484224 entirely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
 upon your own ability. And - generally speaking you progressed, for a normal child of average ability would progress - from standard one up to standard seven - year by year but a really dull scholar would stay down at the bottom in the school all his
 life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How long did it take you from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh I suppose when I was very young probably my brother took me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
But after that - there was only one main road to cross and that - wasn't a very, very busy road by present standards.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Back at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh more or less I - I enjoyed school. I can't say that - my life in the 
elementary school was unpleasant at all. I - was interested in - in learning. And I was interested in playing too you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 What did you feel about your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh some I liked and some I didn't. There was one old spinster - she lived to be abo
ut seventy or eighty - but one old spinster who was a real dragon, and was really thoroughly hated and - most people were - were afraid of her in school. On the other hand there were other teachers we were - we were very fond of. They very as they do toda
y. They've still got the same - same types in school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life, punctuality, cleanliness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Manners, ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. In those days - specially the school I went
 to, those things were - more or less insisted upon as part of education. You had to be neat and tidy, your shoes were to be cleaned, you were to be clean and very often - inspections took place, very often in - in the schoolyard before you - entered scho
ol you see. Oh yes, there was a great insistence upon - the fact that - apart from what you learned in school there were the - neatness and tidiness were - were considered - just as important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 If you did something that was disapproved of by your teachers what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Oh - the cane was there. We never objected to it. We - we - we more or less took it that if we'd - done something we shouldn't have done, well we were to be punished for it and - I can't see any harm has come to me through it - 
over the years. Nor can I say of those - my own - scholars that I meet in every walk of life today - ever hold it against me that I - punished them from time to time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would girls be punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. They were mixed classes - and they were punished, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 They were caned also were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I can't recall any specific incident but - they were subjected to the same rules of discipline. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Can you remember for what particular offences you would be caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Probabl
y - probably talking - talking in class or particularly dirty work or untidy work. You see, there was a great insistence in those days on the three R's. Reading, writing and arithmetic. They were the - the basis, as they must be today, the basis of - of -
 
academic knowledge. And there was a great insistence upon them. There were none of the extra - branches of the curriculum you have in schools today. You see, the school week now is only as long as it was then. But in those days probably - fifty to seventy
-
five percent of the time was spent on the three R's. Giving us a good groundwork in it. Today - perhaps - no more than twenty-five to thirty percent is spent on those - basic subjects you see. You see, you can only - you can't get a quart into a pint pot.
 Your school week is only as long as it was then. And if you're going to bring all these extraneous subjects then you've got to take time off - off some of the others you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
That is one reason, there's no doubt about it, why - why the standard of spelling and - today is so very, very poor compared with what it was in those days. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Because of little - }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  less time spent on those things nowadays.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Only to the extent - my mother probably far 
more than my father. As I say, my father's time was occupied with his own work and church but mother used to take an interest in what we did and - but - you see - mother never had so very much schooling nor did my father, because they belonged to an age w
hen they - they had to pay fourpence a week to go to school. And that was a lot in those days for a poor working family. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did they ask what you did at school or ever visit the school or meet your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 The only time I can imagine parents 
going to school in those days - was when there was some question of - punishment involved. A child, according to the parent, might have been over punished or punished - unnecessarily and the parent might go up and remonstrate. But not in my case. The atti
tude at home was, well if you - if you've been punished you've done something wrong and you deserve what you got. And that is the - the policy I always - have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 adopted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  with my own children. When they came home and said they had the cane I said, well what's it for? I told them they deserved it, probably ought to have had twice as much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Yes. Some from probably poorer types. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 
Of course those were the days, you know, when - as I say, there was no social security and some used to come to school very, very poorly dressed, very very poorly shod. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
And there was a - a Pearson boot fund in operation in those days. Where by - very poor parents could apply through the school authorities for free pairs of footwear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you ever remember any of the children being singled out by the teachers for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You mean favouritsm. Not particularly, no, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were there any gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Inside the school, no. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Were there any children who you felt particularly to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not particularly, no. No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You went on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Oh, when I left - this is Graville, I -
 I was in the infants there, then into the elementary school, from there I got a - I passed an exam which took me to - Hanley High School, you see, I was there from what - 19 - 1917 to - that's right - about 1917 to 1920 - beginning of 1922. So those were
 the only two schools I had, at Granville, at the elementary school, and Hanley High School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Did you go on to college from there or did you go straight into teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I did - no - I - became a student teacher. The large sum of fifty pounds a year
. You had to do before you entered the teaching profession in those days you had to do twelve months student teachership where you more or less - occasionally took a; class but more or less - you absorbed - the atmosphere of the school and you knew what i
t
 was all about. Unlike you do today, and I think - we could very well reserve - revert to that system because then, a new entrant into the profession would know whether or not he was going to like it or not you see. Then you could after your twelve months
 
then, apply to go to college. Well we couldn't afford it and I had - I became what was called an uncertificated teacher for about - nearly two years. And I - had charge of a class and I was - I think I got about a hundred pounds a year for it. No, eighty 
pounds a year. And - I had full responsibility for a class. Until I went into college in 1924. I came out in 1926 a fully qualified teacher you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You did the degree after that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Then I did degree work after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You did that at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well I took some of it in college you see. Then I took some of it - afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How old were you when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 finally}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224  left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 When I left college? Oh - '26 - I should be nearly - just about a month or so off being - '26 - twenty-two years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Would you have continued your education had you had the opportunity, would you have carried on any longer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 I would have liked to have gone into university actually, but - financial arrangements - you see, there were no grants in those 
days. You - it had got to come entirely out of the family resources.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 You continued with your part time education, evening classes and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Not evening classes, no, I studied at home. Yes. Studied at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Do you have any regrets at all about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 
Well as I say I would have liked to have gone into university. Again by reason of - even when I was in college, by reason of financial - conditions at home I was - I had to make what pocket money I had go a long
 way, I was never so - well furnished with money as a good many of my contemporaries in college you see and I - at times I might have been a bit envious of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 How do you think you particularly benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid468979 AH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 Well attending c
ollege, I'll put it this way, it - my horizons were widened vastly. Yes, I came back - having been away from home you see, for the first time - and living - a community life in college, I came back with - with entirely different ideas of the - of the worl
d at large you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8402685\charrsid15484224 And - from the narrow confines of the - the rather narrow horizons of home life I came back - a very, very altered person you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6229036\charrsid15484224 And - that's why I always advise people who are - to leave home and - and go into college or university as the case may be because - you can't explain it to them but they come back a - with a different outlook on life.

